
Here are the things to do after installing a new linux

1. Update the system

	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt-get upgrade

2. Install Chromium
	sudo apt-get install chromium-browser

3. Install multimedia codecs

	sudo apt-get install ubuntu-restricted-extras
	sudo apt-get install libdvdread4
	sudo /usr/share/doc/libdvdread4/install-css.sh

4. Install proprietary drivers

5. Install a clibboard manager
	
	(diodon is one but has issues on cinnamon dekstop)
	sudo apt-get install glipper
	or 
	sudo apt-get install clipit

6. Optimize font rendering
	Noto font
	Droid font

7. Install Guake drop down terminal or Yakuake

	sudo apt-get install guake
	or
	sudo apt-get install yakuake

	go to System Settings -> Startup Programs and add a new one /usr/bin/guake or /usr/bin/yakuake

8. Install a download manager
	sudo apt-get install uget

9. Install System Information tool ( hardware )
	sudo apt-get install hardinfo

10. Install System Monitoring tool
	sudo apt-add-repository -y ppa:teejee2008/ppa
	sudo apt-get update
	sudo apt-get install conky-manager

At the end cleanup
	sudo apt-get autoremove
